5to. That the Lords upon the 21 of July the ſaid year, (as Durie aiſo obſerves in the paralele Caſe betwixt Hamiltoun contra 

                      _____ 
                   ) declare they will decide that Caſe of Hamiltouns, as they did in the foreſaid Caſe of Caſſie contra Fleming: So that the practice of Scotland, has eſtabliſhed it as a principle, that durante cauſa metus nunquam purgatur nutus; And therefore that what is medio tempore done by the party Laeſed, can never import an Homologation of the Tranſaction Meticuloſa.
